<final_answer>
I attempted to list your GitHub SSH keys but none were returned. I can't delete a key without knowing which one it is.

Please let me know which of the following you want me to do:
- Retry listing your linked SSH keys (I'll call the listing tool again).  
- Delete a specific key: paste the key's fingerprint or the key text (or the comment attached to it) and I'll delete that exact key.  
- If you want all SSH keys removed, confirm that and I will attempt to remove them (I still need the current keys to perform the deletions).

If you're not sure how to get the fingerprint/comment from GitHub: go to https://github.com/settings/keys and copy the "Key" or the comment/fingerprint shown next to the key. Send that here and I will delete it for you.
